Whisk egg whites adding the sugar slowly.Cut and split the vanilla pod.  Bring the milk and vanilla to gentle simmer.Using 2 large dessertspoons, quenelle the meringue on to the milk and gently poach each side for around 30-40 seconds.  Remove and put on fruit compote and serve.Sprinkle the mixed berries with vanilla sugar to taste.  Warm berries and sugar in a pan and serve with poached meringues.If using fresh seasonal fruit, cook for longer until the fruit is softened.